    <h1>CRM</h1><div class="paragraph">
<p>In this area, you will find all information about creating and editing <a href="/en/crm/managing-customer-data#800"><strong>customer data records</strong></a> - from the address via orders to tickets, documents, <a href="/en/basics/statistics/customer-statistics"><strong>statistics</strong></a> etc. Create <a href="/en/crm/managing-customer-data#100"><strong>customer classes</strong></a>, <a href="/en/crm/managing-customer-data#300"><strong>customer types</strong></a> and use the <a href="/en/crm/managing-customer-data#3900"><strong>discount system</strong></a> in plentymarkets.</p>
</div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Furthermore, learn how to use the <a href="/en/crm/using-the-ticket-system"><strong>ticket system</strong></a> for your customer communication and how to retain control over orders that are still unpaid with the help of the <a href="/en/crm/managing-customer-data"><strong>AR list</strong></a>.</p>
</div><div class="paragraph">
<p>All emails that are sent with plentymarkets are based on email templates. You can define up to two attachments for each email template. In this area, you will learn how to <a href="/en/crm/sending-emails#1200"><strong>create email templates</strong></a>.</p>
</div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Set up a <a href="/en/crm/sending-newsletters"><strong>newsletter</strong></a> in order to inform your customers at regular intervals about news in your online store. For this purpose, you can set up the newsletter that is integrated in plentymarkets or you set up an interface to <a href="/en/crm/sending-newsletters#1700"><strong>CleverReach</strong></a> or <a href="/en/crm/sending-newsletters#2100"><strong>Newsletter2Go</strong></a>.</p>
</div><div class="paragraph">
